JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 241
EP  - 252
VL  - 22
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - A field study was conducted over a 14 month period to examine goal setting as a dyadic, role making process between 46 managerial and staff employees (subordinates) and 15 officers and directors (supervisors) in an insurance company. Significant improvements in the goal behaviors and significant declines in stress were found following training.
AB  - A field study was conducted over a 14 month period to examine goal setting as a dyadic, role making process between 46 managerial and staff employees (subordinates) and 15 officers and directors (supervisors) in an insurance company. Significant improvements in the goal behaviors and significant declines in stress were found following training.
