T1  - The Impact Of The Computer On The Choice Activity Of Decision Makers: A Replication With Actual Users Of Computerized Mis
AU  - Koester, Robert
AU  - Luthans, Fred
Y1  - 1979/06/01
PY  - 1979
DA  - 1979/06/01
N1  - doi: 10.5465/255600
DO  - 10.5465/255600
T2  - Academy of Management Journal
JF  - Academy of Management Journal
JO  - AMJ
SP  - 416
EP  - 422
VL  - 22
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - The article presents a study that examines the impact of computers, particularly management information systems, on managerial decision making. According to the results of the study, computer users with a high level of experience are less likely to be influenced by information that is computer generated than they are by information that is presented in mimeograph form. Inexperienced users are more influenced by information generated by computers than by information presented in the form of a mimeograph.
AB  - The article presents a study that examines the impact of computers, particularly management information systems, on managerial decision making. According to the results of the study, computer users with a high level of experience are less likely to be influenced by information that is computer generated than they are by information that is presented in mimeograph form. Inexperienced users are more influenced by information generated by computers than by information presented in the form of a mimeograph.
