JO  - AMJ
SP  - 313
EP  - 324
VL  - 22
IS  - 2
PB  - Academy of Management
N2  - An integrative and expanded contextual model for investigating employee intentions to stay or leave an organization is proposed. Four structural/process variables (upward mobility, distributive justice, communication and routinization), one environmental variable (opportunity), one mediating variable (job satisfaction), and four demographic variables (occupation, age, education, and sex) are significant.
AB  - An integrative and expanded contextual model for investigating employee intentions to stay or leave an organization is proposed. Four structural/process variables (upward mobility, distributive justice, communication and routinization), one environmental variable (opportunity), one mediating variable (job satisfaction), and four demographic variables (occupation, age, education, and sex) are significant.
